"/> IRS Publication 17 says that you have to keep tax records for as
long as necessary to support a tax return until the period of
limitations runs out. This period runs out after 3 years unless
an item of income you didn't report is more than 25% of the income
shown on the return, in which case it's 6 years after you filed the
return.

